description: Smallest order for which there are n nonisomorphic finite groups, or 0 if no such order exists.
comments: R. Keith Dennis conjectures that there are no 0's in this sequence. See A053403 for details.
references: H.-U. Besche and B. Eick, Construction of Finite Groups, Journal of Symbolic Computation, Vol. 27, No. 4, Apr 15 1999, pp. 387-404.
H.-U. Besche and B. Eick, The Groups of Order at Most 1000 Except 512 and 768, Journal of Symbolic Computation, Vol. 27, No. 4, Apr 15 1999, pp. 405-413.
J. H. Conway et al., The Symmetries of Things, Peters, 2008, p. 209.
